who needs a constitution anyway.  All we need are laws.  A constitution does nothing but give people a way to break rules.  No one ever wants to talk about the constitution until it helps them in some way.  Who gives a crap about someones right to have children,  I have a right to quit supporting his kids.  The constitution doesn't make the USA a better place.  If anything it hurts us.  Look at the past.  It took one person screaming about it being unconstitutional for prayers in school.  You know what, just for that whiner we dropped prayers for school and you know what we got in return?  Guns.  Lots of them.  Kids lost their morals about that same time.  You dont like prayers in school?  Cover your ears, I like the morals and values that these prayers bestow on our young ones.  I am not religious by any means, in fact I would consider myself an atheist (sp).  I still feel the Bible is a great book to live by.  So if you want a peice of paper that tells you what you can and cant do, throw that piece of paper called The Constitution away and put the  King James version in its place.<br>
