<br>
The bible has good morals to live by yes.  But the second we make IT the law of the land, it becomes how you have described our Constitution.  A means of persecution (eg salem witch trials).  That book is even more open to interpretation than is the constitution.  The Constitution is a brilliant piece of writing because the words contained within have stood the test of time.  Is it perfect?  No!  Will it ever be?  No.  It was written by man. (as was the bible btw).  Man is fallable.  Does it need to be altered from tiem to time?  Yep.  The true genius of that document stands in the fact that built in was the right to change it.  And this has happened many times over the course of the last 250 years.  These are called Ammendments.    The first ten being the Bill of Rights.<br>
<br>
NEway.  Do I think this imbecile should have any more kids?  good gods no!  He is a miserable excuse for a human being and a dishonor to the male half of our species. Should the courts say he CAN'T have any more kids.  Well...  I am not sure.  But I think that any woman that has a child with him had better understand what she is getting into.  Who knows, one of these children may turn out to be the next Martin Luther King, or JFK.  Or Einstein.  Who knows.<br>
<br>
To sum up:<br>
<br>
Constitution:  Good, and good guidline to run a country.<br>
Bible:  Good fiction book full of great morals to live your personal life by.  A HORRIBLE way to run a country.<br>
The idiot in question:  well, he's an idiot and shouldn't have any more kids.<br>
